      • isEmpty

        public static <I> boolean isEmpty(I value)
        Verifies if the passed value of the identifier is empty.

        Always returns false for long and integer values.

        For string and message identifiers, the method verifies the values.

        A string identifier is empty, if it contains an empty string.

        Type Parameters:
        I - the type of the identifier
        Parameters:
        value - the value to check
        Returns:
        true if the identifier is empty; false otherwise

      • checkSupported

        public static <I> void checkSupported(java.lang.Class<I> idClass)
        Ensures that the passed class of identifiers is supported.

        The following types of IDs are supported:

        • String
        • Long
        • Integer
        • A class implementing Message

        Consider using Message-based IDs if you want to have typed IDs in your code, and/or if you need to have IDs with some structure inside.

        Here are the examples of such structural IDs:

        • EAN value used in bar codes
        • ISBN
        • Phone number
        • Email address as a couple of local-part and domain
        Type Parameters:
        I - the type of the ID
        Parameters:
        idClass - the class of IDs
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the class of IDs is not of supported type

      • pack

        public static <I> com.google.protobuf.Any pack(I id)
        Wraps the passed ID value into an instance of Any.

        The passed value must be of one of the supported types listed below. The type of the value wrapped in to the returned instance is defined by the type of the passed value:

        • For classes implementing Message — the value of the message itself
        • For String — StringValue
        • For Long — Int64Value
        • For Integer — Int32Value
        Type Parameters:
        I - the type of the value
        Parameters:
        id - the value to wrap
        Returns:
        instance of Any with the passed value
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the passed value is not of the supported type

      • unpack

        public static java.lang.Object unpack(com.google.protobuf.Any any)
        Extracts ID object from the passed Any instance.

        Returned type depends on the type of the message wrapped into Any:

        • String for unwrapped StringValue
        • Integer for unwrapped Int32Value
        • Long for unwrapped Int64Value
        • unwrapped Message instance if its type is none of the above
        Parameters:
        any - the ID value wrapped into Any
        Returns:
        unwrapped ID

      • toString

        public static <I> java.lang.String toString(I id)
        Converts the passed ID value into the string representation.
        Type Parameters:
        I - the type of the ID
        Parameters:
        id - the value to convert
        Returns:
        • for classes implementing Message — a JSON form;
        • for String, Long, Integer — the result of Object.toString();
        • for null ID — the NULL_ID;
        • if the result is empty or a blank string — the EMPTY_ID.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the passed type isn't one of the above or the passed Message instance has no fields
        See Also:
        StringifierRegistry
